.TH CHROOT "1" "April 2026" "GNU coreutils 9.11" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
chroot \- run command or interactive shell with special root directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B chroot
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]... \fI\,NEWROOT \/\fR[\fI\,COMMAND \/\fR[\fI\,ARG\/\fR]...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\" Add any additional description here
.PP
Run COMMAND with root directory set to NEWROOT.
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#chroot--groups'\fB\-\-groups=G_LIST\fP\X'tty: link'
specify supplementary groups as g1,g2,..,gN
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#chroot--userspec'\fB\-\-userspec=USER:GROUP\fP\X'tty: link'
specify user and group (ID or name) to use
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#chroot--skip-chdir'\fB\-\-skip\-chdir\fP\X'tty: link'
do not change working directory to '/'
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/chroot#chroot--help'\fB\-\-help\fP\X'tty: link'
display this help and exit
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/chroot#chroot--version'\fB\-\-version\fP\X'tty: link'
output version information and exit
.PP
If no command is given, run '"$SHELL" \fB\-i\fR' (default: '/bin/sh \fB\-i\fR').
.SS "Exit status:"
.TP
125
if the chroot command itself fails
.TP
126
if COMMAND is found but cannot be invoked
.TP
127
if COMMAND cannot be found
.TP
\-
the exit status of COMMAND otherwise
